texts.text: Josh 'rockenroll4life' Letellier is a former member of the Minecraft: Java Edition development team at Mojang Studios from July 16, 2018 to April 10, 2019.[1][2] Previously, he worked at the Minecraft Redmond office.
He also owns a YouTube account rockenroll4life where he uploads Minecraft Let's Plays.
On April 10, 2019, Letellier announced his temporary departure from Mojang as his residency/work extension was denied by the Swedish Migration Agency.[3][4]

"Oh boy, am I excited. I'll be flying over to Stockholm this Saturday and should hopefully be starting sometime soon after that. #Hype! I look forward to exploring the city and starting work on the Java edition of @Minecraft! :D" – @rockenroll4life on Twitter, July 11, 2018
"Ah ha! Found it! @Mojang" – @rockenroll4life on Twitter, July 16, 2018

"[1/2] Hey Everyone, It comes with heavy heart that I have to announce that due to complications with Swedish Migrations my residency/work extension was denied and I'm no longer able to work in Sweden or at Mojang for the time being. (Unless some miracle happens)" – @rockenroll4life on Twitter, April 10, 2019

"[2/2] While I may be flying back to the states soon fear not! I hope to return again to the Java team if/when I'm allowed to in the not too distant future! I'm not a quitter! I still got stuff I want to get added and do in Minecraft!" – @rockenroll4life on Twitter, April 10, 2019
